<subSubSection id="C36898C2A674FF99FF33FEFA4734FE24" pageId="5" pageNumber="448" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BCDCB49A674FF99FF33FEFA4734FE24" blockId="5.[151,1437,151,645]" pageId="5" pageNumber="448">
<emphasis id="B906175BA674FF99FF33FEFA4714FE7C" bold="true" box="[199,334,367,392]" pageId="5" pageNumber="448">Etymology.</emphasis>
The name, 
<taxonomicName id="4C72B0CAA674FF99FE28FEE54406FE7C" box="[476,604,368,392]" class="Insecta" family="Sphecidae" genus="Podalonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="448" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bicellularis">
<emphasis id="B906175BA674FF99FE28FEE54406FE7C" box="[476,604,368,392]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="448">bicellularis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, derived from the Latin 
<emphasis id="B906175BA674FF99FC8AFEE545CEFE7C" box="[894,916,368,392]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="448">bi</emphasis>
- (= two), and Latin 
<emphasis id="B906175BA674FF99FB7DFEE542A9FE7C" box="[1161,1267,368,392]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="448">cellularis</emphasis>
(= wing cell), refers to the forewing with two submarginal cells, which is one recognition characters of this species. It is a feminine adjective.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C36898C2A674FF99FF33FE4944BBFD70" pageId="5" pageNumber="448" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BCDCB49A674FF99FF33FE4944BBFD70" blockId="5.[151,1437,151,645]" pageId="5" pageNumber="448">
<emphasis id="B906175BA674FF99FF33FE494773FE01" bold="true" box="[199,297,476,501]" pageId="5" pageNumber="448">Remark</emphasis>
. Most species of this genus from 
<collectingCountry id="F3658BD9A674FF99FD37FE49455CFE01" box="[707,774,476,501]" name="China" pageId="5" pageNumber="448">China</collectingCountry>
have three submarginal cells in the forewing. This new species is remarkable in having only two submarginal cells. However, this may not be a constant feature, because variation in the number of submarginal cells has been observed in 
<taxonomicName id="4C72B0CAA674FF99FC8BFDB14208FDC8" box="[895,1106,548,572]" class="Insecta" family="Sphecidae" genus="Podalonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="448" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="parvula">
